# TTS Cleanup — Code Review & Architecture Walkthrough

## Overview
The TTS Cleanup feature converts AI-written scripts to TTS-ready text by normalizing numbers, abbreviations, acronyms, symbols, and casing via an AI API call.

---

## Architecture Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["🔊 TTS Tab (UI)"] --> B["Scan Folder / Add Files"]
    B --> C["TreeWidget: file list with ✓ checkboxes"]
    C --> D["Process button"]
    D --> E{"Language mismatch warning?"}
    E -->|No| F["_run_cleanup()"]
    E -->|Yes, user confirms| F
    F --> G["ThreadPoolExecutor (N threads)"]
    G --> H["process_one() per file"]
    H --> H1["1. Read .txt file"]
    H1 --> H2["2. API call → cleanup_for_tts()"]
    H2 --> H3["3. Validate non-empty"]
    H3 --> H4["4. Write tts_{filename}.txt"]
    H4 --> H5["Collect acronyms"]
    H5 --> I["Export tts_acronyms_report.csv"]
    F --> J{"Verify enabled?"}
    J -->|Yes| K["Sequential verify via verify_tts_content() (Pro model)"]
    K --> L{"Any failures?"}
    L -->|Yes| M["Export tts_verify_report.csv + Show popup"]
    M --> N["User selects files → Rewrite Selected"]
    N --> O["_rewrite_failed(): AI re-cleanup with error context"]
    O --> P["Re-verify & update status"]
```

