## Core Module: [core/tts_cleanup.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/tts_cleanup.py)

### Functions

| Function | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| [detect_language(text)](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/tts_cleanup.py#26-56) | Simple word-frequency detection → `"en"` / `"es"` / `"unknown"` |
| [cleanup_for_tts(text, api, lang, log_callback)](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/tts_cleanup.py#58-117) | Sends text + system prompt to AI. Parses response: cleaned text + `---ACRONYMS---` section. Returns [(cleaned_text, acronyms_list)](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/tts_tab.py#825-930) |
| [verify_tts_content(original, tts, api, lang, log_callback)](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/tts_cleanup.py#119-174) | Compares original vs TTS text via AI (always Pro). Returns JSON `{match, score, issues[]}` |
| [export_acronym_csv(data, path)](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/tts_cleanup.py#176-210) | Writes acronym conversions to CSV (handles locked file with retry) |
| [scan_txt_files(folder, recursive)](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/tts_cleanup.py#212-277) | Discovers [.txt](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/_CRASH_LOG.txt) files, skips system files (`_SUMMARY`, `_VERIFY`, [tts_](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/tts_cleanup.py#119-174) prefix, etc.). Returns file metadata list |

### Key Design Patterns
- **Response parsing**: AI response uses `---ACRONYMS---` separator between cleaned text and acronym table
- **Locked-file retry**: CSV export retries up to 10 times with `_N` suffix if file is locked
- **Skip patterns**: `_SUMMARY`, `_VERIFY`, `_STATUS`, `_MERGE`, `_REORDER`, `FULL_SCRIPT`, `_PREVIEW`, `_STYLE_`, `_REWRITE_STATUS`, [tts_](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/tts_cleanup.py#119-174) prefix

